1. Objects in JavaScript

ðŸ‘‰ Objects basically keyâ€“value pairs hote à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚.
à¤¹à¤° key ek property à¤¯à¤¾ method à¤¹à¥‹ à¤¸à¤•à¤¤à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤

```js
let person = {
    name: "Kajal",
    age: 22,
    city: "Indore",
    
    // Method (function inside object)
    greet: function() {
        return `Hello, my name is ${this.name}`;
    }
};

console.log(person.name);   // Property access â†’ Kajal
console.log(person.greet()); // Method call â†’ Hello, my name is Kajal

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Methods of Objects:-

Object methods :- keys(), values(), entries(), assign() etc.
Example:-
let student = {
    id: 101,
    name: "Aman"
};

// ðŸ”¹ Object.keys() â†’ sabhi keys return karega
      console.log(Object.keys(student));  
; // ["id", "name"]

// ðŸ”¹ Object.values() â†’ sabhi values return karega
      console.log(Object.values(student));  
;   [101, "Aman"]

// ðŸ”¹ Object.entries() â†’ [key, value] pairs return karega
      console.log(Object.entries(student));  
; // [["id", 101], ["name", "Aman"]]

// ðŸ”¹ Object.assign() â†’ ek object ke properties dusre me copy karega
let extra = { age: 20 };
Object.assign(student, extra);
console.log(student); 
; // { id: 101, name: "Aman", age: 20 }
```
